The paper deals with a data structure for representing sets of vectors and answering queries based on their Hamming distance. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves analyzing the space usage of the data structure, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of Bloom filters suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
